{{coord|4|15|S|15|25|E|display=title}}
'''Mbamu''' (also: '''M´Bamou''' and '''Bamu''') is an island in the [[Republic of the Congo]] (Congo Brazzaville). It is situated in the [[Pool Malebo]], a lake formed by the [[River Congo]] and has surface area of 180&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref name="britannica">[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/359978/Malebo-Pool "Malebo Pool"]. [http://www.britannica.com Encyclopædia Britannica]. Accessed June 2017.</ref> To the south lies [[Kinshasa]] and to the northwest lies [[Brazzaville]].

